# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your values.
# .env.local is gitignored and will never be committed.

# GitHub integration uses Personal Access Tokens (PAT) — no OAuth App needed.
# Users generate a classic PAT at github.com/settings/tokens with scopes:
#   repo, read:user
# The token is entered in the app's Settings screen and stored in SecureStore.
# No environment variables are required for GitHub auth.
